"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The sb.lineplot function expects a DataFrame or a long-form array as the data parameter. When data is set to None, x and y should be column names from the DataFrame provided in the data parameter. Here, x and y are being passed as arrays directly, which is not the correct usage of the seaborn lineplot API.\",\n  \"patch\": \"20c20\\n< sb.lineplot(data=None, x=df['X'].values, y=Y_pred.reshape(-1))\\n---\\n> df_new['Y_pred'] = Y_pred.reshape(-1)\\n> sb.lineplot(data=df_new, x='X', y='Y_pred')\\n\"\n}"